The psychology of excess tendering: why spend more money?
At the auctions, buyers are likely to spend more, to overestimate the goods.
Neurologists and economists researchers at the University of New York have managed to discover the neuroeconomic bases of this known and apparently irrational behavior.
According to their study appeared on the Science magazine men don’t want to stay behind in a race such as the eBay auction, so they’re available to pay even a higher price.
The research sought to track the nervous scheme of this "party" at the nervous system level through experimental exchanges.
A group of volunteers played the lottery, the other group of players participated in an auction while using the functional magnetic resonance method (fMRI) they examined the active areas of the brain of the people participating in the experiment.
In both games the participants could win money, but in the auction game, where the essential element is to offer more than the other, the striated body under the brain cortex intensely enters into function when you lose the game.
This area of the brain, in addition to other functions, plays a role in the mechanism of the nervous system’s “autogramation”.
Therefore, according to the researchers, the price rise is explained by scanning the vein reaction of the striated body.
To support their theory, the research group’s economists conducted a financial follow-up survey.
In this investigation, three groups complained against a partner under different conditions.
The control group how much the actual value of the product in question was and they made their pointing.
In addition to this, they promised that in case of victory they will receive another $15 prize.
The third group would receive $15 before the auction, but the group members would lose the money in case of loss at the auction.
The difference between the two groups consisted in the fact that for one of them the victory was highlighted, while for the other the loss.
Understood the hypothesis of the neurologists, the members of the group that played "contra loss" were willing to score higher than the control group or "vinced".
"These findings are not deductible from any of the previously existing economic theories.
In fact, these so far explained the phenomena that can be met at the auctions with the joy of winning and with the avoidance of risk.
Only the methods of creating the neurological image helped solve the contradiction between the two theories, so we came to a third explanation,” said Andrew Schotter, professor of the Faculty of Economics at the University of New York.
Hepatitis: When to go to a doctor?
Nearly half a billion people worldwide suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, but in Hungary among the first causes of death are mentioned chronic liver diseases.
In Hungary, the number of patients with hepatitis rises to a hundred thousand, of which only 7,000 are treated: the reason is that many patients do not know that they are infected.
The definition of hepatitis is the collective name of infectious liver diseases caused by various viruses.
There are many similarities between the symptoms, typical are hepatitis and irritis, but their pathogens and caused diseases differ from each other.
Hepatitis viruses spread in two main forms depending on the pathogen: hepatitis A and E through the food channel (e.g. water and infected foods), hepatitis B, C, D and other viruses with blood and organic fluids (sperm, vaginal loss, saliva).
For travelers it is useful to vaccinate against the virus A and B, against the C there is no vaccine.
The symptoms of hepatitis A appear two to three weeks after eating infected foods, accompanied by general discomfort, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After yellow spots are formed on the skin and on the white of the eyes, the spots become clear and the urine is dark, healing takes place within two to three weeks.
A million people die every year worldwide for hepatitis B, the most severe variant of the disease, which causes liver tumors and liver cirrhosis.
The main reason is, according to estimates, that only one in ten people receive pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: if not treated, it can cause liver cirrhosis and liver tumors.
Most infected people don’t know they’ve contracted the disease because the pathogens sublimely destroy the liver cells, in many cases the first symptoms appear after 20-30 years.
Therefore, it is very important to prevent and perform regular medical tests.
This disease is much more common than the average in three groups: those who had a blood transfusion before 1991, drug addicts and tattoos.
In the world, the number of people infected with the virus of chronic hepatitis C is 200 million.
Since even a routine laboratory examination reveals the disease, it is worth contacting the family doctor when you notice any symptoms of unknown origin.
Recognized in time the disease is healable, the virus can be removed from the body, so the infectious power ceases and the formation of tumors can be prevented.
September 30 is the World Hepatitis Day, organized for the first time in the world in 2004 by associations of patients.
The aim is to draw attention to chronic viral hepatitis, the causes of its development and the early recognition of the disease.
Who believes in God feels less pain?
According to the results of a recent investigation, the religious faith works as a species of analgesic that made the death of Catholic martyrs more tolerable.
Scientists at the University of Oxford conducted an interesting experiment, examining how faith in God influences the feeling of pain, the British Telegraph.
In the framework of this bizarre investigation, a electro-shock was carried out on 12 Catholic believers and atheists, while all of them observed a painting of the Virgin Mary.
According to the results, Catholic believers were able to reject much of the pain.
Thanks to the exploration technique of the human brain it was discovered that Catholics were able to activate the part of the brain responsible for control of pain.
The test is the first of a series of research in which in addition to the academics also participate scientists, philosophers and theologists of the University.
The test took place exactly this way: an instrument that emits outputs and passes the electroshock was connected to the left hand of the subject of the experiment.
The researchers asked the participants to focus on two paintings, the Virgin Mary painted in the 17th century by Sassoferrato and the Lady with the herd of Leonardo da Vinci painted in the 15th century.
The authors of the examination hoped that the image of the Virgin Mary originated a kind of religious state among the believers, while the picture of Leonardo was chosen because it didn’t differ too much from the other and they thought it was a calming effect.
The subjects of the experiment spent half an hour in front of the MRI scanner and in this hour of time they received 20 electroshocks in four consecutive series, while observing either the religious theme painting or the other.
The Catholics that the vision of the Virgin Mary made them feel “safe”, as if “somebody took care” of them and “they were calmed and pervased by peace.”
Looking at the image on religious theme they realized 12% less pain than when they had the work of Leonardo in front of themselves.
The psychologist Miguel Farias, who took part himself in the test, believes that a similar result can be achieved with any image of the strong effect even for the atheists, but it is necessary to find the right image.
“We have to look for an image to which they feed very positive feelings, such as a mother or a father,” the psychologist said.
Anglican bishop Tom Wright was pleased with the result of the research.
“The practice of faith should change, and in many cases it manages to change our personality,” Wright added.
After the great results remains the question if the painting of a Madonna of Leonardo or another painter of a similar calibre is presented to the believers, what effect could it have on pain control?
The vision of a quality Virgin Mary would bring better results?
